From: Alejandro Sáez <asm@redhat.com>
Subject: [PATCH] crypto/tls: fix FIPS expandLabel HKDF performance regression

The expandLabel function in the FIPS patch uses io.ReadAll(r) to read
HKDF output from the OpenSSL backend, with a significant overhead.
The fix replaces io.ReadAll(r) with a single r.Read(out) call using a
properly-sized buffer.

Resolves: OCPBUGS-79679

diff --git a/src/crypto/tls/key_schedule.go b/src/crypto/tls/key_schedule.go
--- a/src/crypto/tls/key_schedule.go
+++ b/src/crypto/tls/key_schedule.go
@@ -113,8 +113,12 @@ func expandLabel(newFunc func() hash.Hash, secret []byte, label string, context
 		if err != nil {
 			panic(err)
 		}
-		b, _ := io.ReadAll(r)
-		return b[:length]
+		out := make([]byte, length)
+		n, err := r.Read(out)
+		if err != nil || n != length {
+			panic("tls: HKDF-Expand-Label invocation failed unexpectedly")
+		}
+		return out
 	}
 	return tls13.ExpandLabel(newFunc, secret, label, context, length)
 }
